   <narrative xml:lang="EN">SL Hotels Asia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Shangri-La Asia Limited (SLA or the Sponsor) is a leading owner and operator of hotels and resorts in Asia. SLA and its subsidiaries (together the Group) own and/or manage 101 hotels in over 20 countries.  Tourism is one of the hardest hit sectors by the COVID-19 pandemic, and there have been severe business disruptions to the operations of the Groups hotel properties as a result. The proposed investment will be to Shangri-La Asia Treasury Limited (SLT or the Company), in order to support the Groups existing operations in Fiji, Maldives, Mongolia and Sri Lanka during this challenging time (the Project).</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">At the Project level, the Project is expected to: (i) sustain the relevant project companies&apos; ability to maintain employment of staff; and (ii) sustain demand for goods and services from the relevant project companies&apos; suppliers so that the project companies and their suppliers could maintain their operations in the current situation.
At the Market level, the Project is expected to: (i) promote the resilience of tourism sector by preserving the availability and quality of goods and services provided by a large regional player; and (ii) preserve the sector&apos;s ability to support the economic recovery effort as conditions normalize.</narrative>
  </description>
